---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="StepFill Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for StepFill — the app collects no data about you and makes no network connections."
>
  <main class="blog-container">
    <h1 class="page-title">StepFill Privacy Policy</h1>
    <section class="prose">
      <p><strong>Last updated: June 5, 2026</strong></p>

      <p>StepFill ("the app") is developed by Yusuke Morishita ("we", "us"). This
      policy explains how the app handles your information. The short version:
      <strong>StepFill does not collect any data about you.</strong></p>

      <h2>No data collection</h2>
      <p>StepFill has no user accounts, no analytics, no advertising, and no
      third-party SDKs. It makes <strong>no network connections of any kind</strong>.
      Nothing you enter is sent to us or to anyone else, because the app has no
      server to send it to.</p>

      <h2>Apple Health (HealthKit)</h2>
      <p>The purpose of StepFill is to let you add step counts to Apple Health and
      review or edit the entries you have saved.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>StepFill requests permission to <strong>write</strong> step data to Apple
        Health (to add, edit, and delete entries) and to <strong>read</strong> your
        step data. Reading is used only on your device, to show your step history and
        to let you edit or delete the entries StepFill saved.</li>
        <li>The step counts and dates you enter are saved to Apple Health on your
        device by the operating system. This data is stored and protected by Apple
        Health, not by us, and it stays on your device (subject to your own iCloud and
        Health settings, which we do not control).</li>
        <li>Your step data is read only on your device and is never transmitted, sold,
        or shared. We (the developer) never receive it. It is never used for
        advertising or marketing.</li>
        <li>You can review or delete anything StepFill has written at any time in the
        Health app: <strong>Browse &gt; Activity &gt; Steps &gt; Show All Data</strong>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data we store about you</h2>
      <p>None. StepFill keeps no profile, identifiers, or usage records.</p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>StepFill does not collect personal information from anyone, including children.</p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>If this policy changes, we will update the date above and post the new version
      at this URL.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@yusuke.ca">hello@yusuke.ca</a>.</p>
    </section>
    <a href="/stepfill/terms" class="blog-post-back">Terms of Service &rarr;</a>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
